caption: Amazing thai food each time!
Great Thai place. We tried the drunken noodles, wonton soup and Ka prow, everything was delicious.
It has nothing to do with titanic and eating on a scale of 1 to 10 will eventually score 1!!!!!! 😠😠
A classic DC establishment with delicious food and a nice staff.

Unvelievably bad. Don't waste your money. This was ThaiTanic before, which was pretty good for a while before the standard really started to fall. Good to know the rebranding to Ammathar hasn't changed a thing. Still overcooked to the point of chewy, way too sweet, sad ingredients, and sometimes just straight up weird flavors.
Don’t think twice and come and support this local business owner. The owner who’s also the chef is very friendly and his food is very delicious.

OMG!¿???  Is it good? No, it's Par Excellent!☆☆☆☆☆☆  By far, one of the best Thai restaurants outside of Bangkok!!! The menu is extensive and will take several visits to manage. In time you will discover your fav's...
Great Thai food, tasted authentic from Thai customer.

Very good. I got the Pad See Mao with vegetables for take out. The level of spiciness is ON POINT. This dish is not lathered in salt. Price is good for the way it appears to be prepared. It looks like the vegetables were grilled, I don't believe it was ever frozen. The noodles do not taste frozen. This is great.

Pad Thai was just Ok. Shrimp in pad Thai was horrible. Overcooked, no flavor. Disappointed. Pad Thai is a signature Thai dish and should always be good in my opinion. Go elsewhere, perhaps Amina Thai in Silver Spring, MD, you will he impressed!

Service: 1/5 Food: 3/5  After seeing so many good reviews online, I decided to bring my friend visiting from out of town here on Saturday night. We waited 15 minutes to be seated even though there were empty tables for us. Took almost 40 minutes for fried calamari, potpourri mussels and Tom kha to come out and it was all cold when it finally did. After having to wait another 10 minutes to get the servers attention he was able to fix the problem.  Once warm the calamari  was really good, tom kha decent and mussels only okay. We ordered Pad thai to come out after the soup and apps. Flavor was good, but noodles were very greasy and extremly salty.  We ordered a couple mixed drinks from the bar, which were surprisingly good and perhaps the best part of the meal.  Would not reccomend to a friend and I will likely not be back.

We like a lot to go out. Last night we arrived in this fine restaurant which friends told us about. We enjoyed a lovely evening there with very good dishes and an efficient stuff and  a professional  cuisine. We put this fine restaurant in our phone list  and we will definitely come back soon.  Highly recommended.
Fabulous food. Super spicy and full of flavor.
One of the best Thai places I've ever been to! I absolutely will be back!
food was very good!
Excellent food. I will come back in the near future
Agree, Tom Yam is really good here. Drunken Noodles are spicy and flavorful. Staff s very friendly. I sure, will be coming back.
Never dined inside, always take food carry-out. Their food is really, really good. Pad Thai is the best in town and their Tom Yam is also great.
Meh. Good Thai iced tea.

So we walked in 3 of us we didn't want the booth by the door so we walked to the one in the back... mind you the place is empty like 3 tables, as we get to the back booth it seats 6 but its 830... so I said we'd like that table, the host stated we couldn't because it was for a reservation... no reservation sign but ok... we sit eat our meal...last customers by closing... no reservation on the booth for 6!  You have a pathetic liar on staff and doesn't care about your customers... I'm sure if it wasnt for the place upstairs  closing you wouldn't have had those 3 tables to begin with.  When u arent making sales  giving your customers the simplest kind gesture would go a long way  we were going for a huge meal with drink but after that greeting we ate light and had water!  All thanks you the liar!
Perfect food and ambiance.
Classic DC thai resturaunt back when 14th street was a skid. Great classic dishes. I'm a fan of the Birds Nest dish because its Spicy
Excellent choice for Thai food, very rich flavor and fresh products are used on every plate. Make sure you try the Wonton soup, simply delicious!!!
Great service and food! Enjoyed my Pad Kee Mao a bit spicy but not over the top!
Excellent food & services...👍
I ordered Pad Thai with tofu extra spicy to go. The dish had pieces of pork in it and zero spice, it didn’t taste bad but it was not what I ordered. Friendly staff, however I would not go again.

(Translated by Google) First time I expect Thai food. I loved it very different, very good taste very worth going  (Original) Primeira vez que esperimento comida tailandesa. Eu amei bem diferente , sabor muito bom vale muito a pena ir
My last meal if ever required to choose.  Bird's nest on fire is my number one dish. Sauted chicken in a bed of kale.
Food was so greasy. Don’t have any type of sauce! Not even soy sauce. And disrespectful table service.
Good food, pleasant atmosphere.  Clearly a favorite place for locals as they were doing solid trade in called in called ahead orders.
It was just meh.

Food was delicious, plating was pretty. It wasn't packed so the service was fast. The only thing I can say negative is that no rice comes with the larb gai nor the som tom (papaya salad)  I'm half Thai and i know rice comes with all that lol

The best Thai food in DC. I’m not Thai but I love Thai food and I eat Thai food four or five days a week. I used to live in DC, and I would go to the Thai Tanic very often.  While I’m not living in DC anymore, every time when I visit DC I always go back to the Thai Tanic. The food is so delicious, the staff is so nice and friendly especially the owner. He is so welcome and so kind.
Haven’t been there but, really want to visit once in my life. Best wishes from Afghanistan

We ordered take out. Both dishes were very good. We got the combo stir fried vegetables with pork and Thai Titanic Star.  added a side of chili garlic sauce. Very excellent! It’s slightly sweet but only a little, then the heat sneaks up. We saved the rest in a jar. I like that their menu has more than the standard Thai items.
Delicious and Hearty Portions. Service is wonderful
Really good thai food! Green curry with spice level 3 is really tasty! Good restaurant to stop by for a quick dinner. Great service!

(Translated by Google) Great service, great food, great quality. I highly recommend it. If you are in Washington DC, do not miss this restaurant. The nearest metro stations are the red line: Dupon Circle and / or Farragut North, then just use GPS that has no error.  (Original) Ótimo atendimento, comida excelente de ótima qualidade. Eu recomendo. Caso você esteja em Washington DC, não deixe de conhecer este restaurante. As estações de metrô mais próximas são da linha vermelha: Dupon Circle e/ou Farragut North, depois é só usar o GPS que não tem erro.
Excellent place. Go, you won't be sorry.
So many good dishes here, like the Nua Ka Ting. Strips of savory beef covered in a spicy sauce topped with toasted basil leaves. One of my favorites. This is my go-to place for Thai, hands down.

Order Chicken Pad Thai through Postmates. It is pretty bland despite ordering it medium spicy. Not very flavorful at all. Had to add chicken as an extra, it wasn’t available in the menu as a standard protein.
Great service and amazing food!
Super tasty food, good cocktails, friendly staff.
Very good thai
Great Pad Thai!
Good price quality

The appetizer I came for was great: deep-fried, deboned chicken wings stuffed with chicken, shrimp, and crab (though skimped on crab). My pad Thai, however, tasted like something I'd get in a frozen food aisle -- if I ever dared eat Thai food out of a freezer. (Trader Joe's would probably be an exception.) It was pretty tasteless. The service was very inattentive. I had to catch my server's attention at least three times for things she'd forgotten to bring and for the check. I never got a refill on my water, and it took her a long time to pick up my check. The restaurant was not busy, probably because it was Easter. A mediocre experience never to be repeated.
This place has really good Thai food and the prices are great especially for Downtown. I had the Red Thai Curry with chicken and it was tasty.

An old standby in the neighborhood.  Reasonably priced when most of Logan circle is not.  Their flavors are rich, curries laden with coconut milk.  My friends call the fried rice cracked fried rice because it is so tasty.  The best is fried rice with chicken and added vegetables.  I also tried a cashew chicken that was yum. The noodles are all good.  There is a full bar and if they have it, you must get the mango and sticky rice.
Good atmosphere and friendly staff.
Goong Lava is wonderfu
Love Thai food here so much. It is so Thai style. Recommended!!!!

Was originally going to Baan Thai and accidentally walked into this restaurant which is located directly below it.  We ended up having a great time, great food, and great service. We ordered the sticky rice with mango and they served it in the shape of a heart (Valentine’s Day)  Sometimes it’s best to try a place yourself and be the judge, and not just go off of other people’s experiences. Places change over time for better or worse and as of today we had a great time here.
They did not have MEE KROB, which we had explicitly called beforehand to make sure they had.
Excellent food and reasonable prices. We ate here twice and both meals were delicious and reasonable priced. The atmosphere isn't very good (reminds me of a cheap diner) however the food is great!
Love the chicken Satay

While it may not appear to be much from the outside, the chef clearly knows how to prepare authentic Thai cuisine. Not only was the pad Thai very good but I especially enjoyed the garden roles which were incredibly fresh with a wonderful sauce. The entire menu is certainly worth an opportunity for the discerning palate I will definitely be back. Thanks Tim for a great experience
Yummy food!

The reason for the one star is for the other complaints like ours that has not been addressed. Look at our picture, there we're 4 tables with customers. After 10 minutes, our young female Asian server (with a long ponytail) approached us.  We we we're not ready to order and I told her this. The look on her face was of discust as she walked away. 10 minutes later she came back and took our order.  This was the last we saw of her for the meal until the bill time. She didn't bring any food out or check on our meal.  The food was very good but the service from our server was substandard.
So good. It is actually a better menu than Baan Thai. Same owners different menu concept. If you like central Thai food i.e. recognizable Thai restaurant food, this is the place for you.
The food was good. It got a little crowded around 7. The bad is a bug of some form ran past my plate..
Ordered stir fried vegetables. Very average quality. I could have cooked at home
Great drunken noodles and curries.
The food was okay, but the portions were really small!
Very authentic, if it says „spicy“, it is spicy! Go there, also very good Sapporo Beer.
Excellent girls were awesome
Love the food and the drinks! Chill place to unwind alone or with friends. My goto Thai 🇹🇭 place in the city!
I come here with friends for dinner almost every Friday night. Very casual environment with great food selection, great prices, and incredibly friendly staff. What more can I say?
Really good food but no free re-fill on the lemonade :(

Went for a late lunch and enjoyed a delicious meal for two starting with rolls followed by Chicken and Beef Pad Thai, then roasted banana with ice cream for desert. The waitress was friendly and helpful. Will go back when in the neighborhood.
Best foo in dc❣️😋👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
Be careful with that, or you will pay tips twice. In general, the food is great and very tasty.
A terrible experience. Least Thai restaurant I would go...
I really enjoyed this place. The staff was very friendly and accommodating. The seating was warm and cozy. Great place for romance!
Small place but great food. Not too spicy. We loved it
I really love here. So delicious.😀
Fantastic food, great service, friendly neighborhood.  Bravo!

My favorite restaurant in DC. Came here pretty much every week over the 2 months I was in DC. Ordered something different each time and every dish was delicious. I always came with my friend from Thailand. She even speaks to the waiters in Thai, so the food is definitely authentic.
I had duck noodle and my friend had lard na, both were delicious and authentic
Great food
While the Thai iced tea was on point, the rest of the meal was either stale or burned. Cool name, though.
The Panang Curry and Pad Kee Mow were incredible. Fresh, delicious, reasonably priced, some of the best Thai food I’ve had at any price. Beautiful.
Delicious Pad Thai!!
Very good food, quick service.

(Translated by Google) Service a bit slow ... the food is delicious. We ordered a Chicken Pad Pad and Papaya Salad and it was delicious. Reasonable portion price.  (Original) שירות קצת איטי... האוכל טעים. הזמנו פאד תאי עוף וסלט פפאיה והיה טעים. מחיר מנה סביר.
FIVE STAR RATING FOR NAME. Never been there, but it's on my list.  But I'm fully impressed with everything I've scene.

[WATCH OUT FOR THE SERVICE FEE!] Been there a few times (like 5). The food is good, but the service we received was terrible. Recently two of us walked into the empty room for lunch (there were only two other customers there) and the waitress led us to a small two-person table. We asked to be seated in a bigger one because there was like no one else in the room...though approved, she hesitated a bit and rolled her eyes. That was acceptable but the next day we went there again, it was a different waitress, and in the end, she charged us an extra 18% service fee that we had never had before. We called her about the issue and she came to take at the bill for about half a minute, then went "you never had it before?" We said no and then she went back to take off the extra service fee. Unbelievable! Never went there again...
The birds nest on fire is one if the best meals I've ever had!

The taste of the food was average- although slightly bland and luke warm when we received it, but I'm taking off one star off due to the service. We ordered the koh moo yang or grilled pork with sticky rice as an appetizer and received an unnamed beef dish that we didn't order. When we told our waitress what happened, she proceeded to tell us off that we didn't pronounce the grilled pork dish correctly and blamed us for the mistake. By this point, our entrees had already arrived so we cancelled the grilled pork appetizer. At the end of the meal, the waitress dropped off a carryout bag with the beef dish that we never ordered and we were charged for the grilled pork appetizer with no explanation or follow-up. There are much better Thai restaurants on the block that won't treat their customers with the disrespect that was shown at Thaitanic.
(Translated by Google) Authentic, delicious  (Original) 正宗 好吃

Never disappoints. Great food selection at a standard Thai restaurant price. Descriptive menu that helps you pick what you want, and you're always able to edit an item if you don't like all ingredients.
Amazing food and fast service. Not far from downtown or the national Mall.
Best Thai I've had. The blinking bar may be a trigger if you have seizures.
Recommend.
Fast service.   Quality food. Spicy if you want it that way Good atmosphere,  relaxed.

The ppl on the phone he was so rude they are telling to study the manu then call them back i told him it was my first time ordering food from there and I worked for hotel we recommend their food but these people doesn't have any manners!!!
Really good that food and interesting looking drinks.

As perhaps the biggest Titanic fan ever, appreciative of great puns, and a lover of Thai food, well this seemed like the perfect place for me to go! But...all life is a game of luck. The entrees were great and well-prepared. I ordered the green curry with chicken and really enjoyed it. Good spice and flavor! Add a Thai iced tea and perfect comfort food dinner. The wait service was on point. However, the appetizers and cocktails seemed over priced for the quality. Perhaps this menu melodrama is what made it Titanic themed, if unfortunately nothing else in the restaurant really was? First class for this Minnesotan. Overall, a place I would return to if I found myself floating through the neighborhood...

Nice little spot!!  We happened across Thaitanic because a restaurant across the street was too crowded. Thaitanic's decor is sort of retro and tables are very close together.  Thaitanic has a full bar and an interesting cocktail menu. All the usual Thai favorites are served up hot, fast and yummy! Prices are reasonable. I enthusiastically  recommend Thaitanic!!

One of the most tasteful Panang Curries I have ever had. Staff is patient and courteous. Parking is really tough to find around the area, especially on weekends. The competitors' situation is funny with Ban Thai directly on the floor above Thaitanic.
Good food, friendly staff
All around average thai restaurant.  The food was good and so was the service.  The menus were huge but i felt like the standard thai platters fell a bit flat (pad thai/drunken noodles)
Great place with a large menu.

I would be willing to give Thai Tanic another try, but it didn't impress this time. I had Lemongrass shrimp soup, which shared the fatal flaw of most saucy shrimp dishes: the tails of the shrimp still had their shells. I understand that the shelling is done in a processing plant somewhere and restaurants don't want to invest hours taking off the remnant, but honestly, for a *soup* it just doesn't work. I had to reach into the oily soup and physically pry off the shell of each shrimp tail. I won't be doing that dish again.  Good service, not too crowded, prices are pretty good (I had a $15 entree and a $7 dessert).
Two Thai restaurants right next to each other. Atmosphere is what is expected from a Thai restaurant in DC. Food is very good.
Highly recommended.
Very goog food.
great menu, very attentive waiting staff, fab portion sizes and could even cater for vegans. Will definitely be going back!

A true gem for food lovers in a city where whitewashing a scrubbing culture from the streets is commonplace- Thaitanic is a go-to spot for folks who love good Thai food for a very reasonable price. Good service, and cool vibe, I've had very consistent experiences. A strict upgrade from the bougie Thai place upstairs.
Great food, very nice service. Awesome vegetarian options. Would recommend!
GREAT SERVICE AND BANGING AZZ FOOD!!!!! LOVED IT!!!
Quick and friendly on a slow Tuesday. Pad Thai arrived fast and was the right level of heat. Good portion size and good quality. I recommend.
Great food and drinks also the service was great

Food was average and the server was unattentive!! Didnt even refill my water!!  I really wanted to not leave a tip, but didn't want her to treat others badly due to my tip. Here's a tip don't be a server if you dont like serving people. One stars due to serve, food 3.5 stars
Dishes are delicious. Staff is super friendly and accommodating. Not pretentious, just good food.
Lovely food, good veggie options
Food came and no one spoke for a good 15 minutes because we were to busy eating. Service is excellent. Great place to end a day of sight seeing.
Food wasn't terrible, but wasn't great either.

One of my favorite Thai spots. Quick to sit down and get your food. Large variety of menu items and the food is delicious. Staff are friendly and the restaurant is clean. I recommend this to all of my friends stopping through town.

Stopped in on a Friday night for a dinner date. We must've arrived just before the dinner rush at 8PM. They have a pretty extensive menu both food and drinks. The grilled squid was really good as an app. We both loved our main dishes too. The friendly service, great food, and social atmosphere will bring us back again!
Great unpretentious spot in the middle of the gentrification on 14th with great food and quality ingredients. I knew it was legit from the Thom Ka Khai alone. Wanted to lick the plate!
Good food, standard

I had a wonderful dinner with my wife. Food was fantastic and it wasn't too loud to talk to each other which was really nice. I ordered a spicy dish, and the only thing I did more than sweat was comment on how delicious it was. We're going to go back again in the next couple of days so we can try one of the other dishes we wanted to try. A real treat.
The menu has a decent vegetarian section.
This place was great - great food and great service. The waiter even took our celebratory photo (we were having our celebratory meal after doing a big bicycle trip). No complaints.
Slow service but the food was great
Love the green curry!
MEAT WAS NOT FRESH! Plenty of amazing and authentic Thai restaurants in the DC area... Sadly, I would not recommend this one.
In my experience, the best Thai food in DC. Warning: spicy means spicy! This place should have a line out the door.
The Pad Thai had no spice nor was I asked if I wanted it spicy. Other than that it was okay.
i like the vegetable fried rice. great!
It's okay. I'd rather go to Taekwood across the street, which is at the same price point but nicer.
Middle of the road Thai food
Three restaurants in one building. One of my favorite places for Thai and sushi.
Love the food, but the staff can be a tad curt.
(Translated by Google) Delicious. Quickly. A bit simple. Therefore - 4!  (Original) Очень вкусно. Быстро. Немного просто. Поэтому - 4!
In the past, Thai food has always been ok for me... But this restaurant has extremely delicious options! Great for dinner with friends and loved ones. One of the best in D.C!!

This is our third Thai restaurant this week and so far it's been the best!  Great prices, great service and very tasteful food.  We were in Connecticut and NY and this place was by far the best.  Please stop by and try it for yourself!
Good Thai and sushi, good service and good prices.
The alcoholic thai ice tea was nice and strong. The curry tasted good, but the meat was overcooked an chewy.
We picked this restaurant on whim. The three of us were very impressed with the service and the speed of the food. We all would eat there again.
Quick and decent Thai food

It is as reliably tasty as Thai food is. Portions are a touch smaller than Sala Thai up on U St, but the prices are a touch less, too. I still feel it's a bit pricey, however, and service can vary between apathetic to rude. But the food's good!  (this review was written in 2012; as of 2015 their service has since become far more friendly!).
sooo soo good!
The food is de-lish and the service was the best. Their fried rice, you must try.
Loved the Thai experience this is my first time, so all I can say is this is the best Thai spot in Washington DC.
Maybe not the most authentic Thai food around, but who cares, I really enjoyed it.  I especially liked the Bird Nest on Fire especially.
We love it. It is just tasteful and well priced
Nearby and tasty.

If you think that this is the best Thai food in DC, your palate isn't that sophisticated. The food is bleh, the service is horrendous and the atmosphere is grimy. I ordered the drunken noodles and it was subpar. Only 5 strips of beef in the entire terrible dish, it tasted like it was a few days old. We also ordered a 2nd entree; fried duck. It should have been called fried duck fat because that's all we had on the plate. That wasn't the worst part. We found mold in the tomato that was on the duck plate. YES A MOLDY TOMATO! I will NEVER EVER go back to this greasy spoon.

Loved the house soup.  A single dish doesn't really fill me up but because the prices are somewhat reasonable I can order multiple items without breaking the bank.  So far I have liked everything I've ordered there.  But I've only visited 3 times.

I never review restaurants, but this one was review-worthy. There was a fly in my soup! Need I say more. All they offered was half off. The crap should have been free after that, as a customer courtesy measure. I left, of course.
Cold beers and pad thai!  Nice joint, very friendly, unpretentious.  I will definitely return.

Tasty and reasonably priced. I do takeout a lot and they're pretty quick about turning around an order. Indoor dining is a good experience as well. I wish they had more booths but it's never stopped me from going.

Staff was very unprofessional. We were seated at 8:00, and at 8:15 we were told the table had been reserved at 9:00, and we were being rudely rushed to order and finish our meal. We left without ordering, but the appetizer was excellent. Too bad the bad service completely overshadowed the good food. Will not be returning.

Thaitanic is a good option for those looking for a quick bite of Thai food. While it's fine to dine in the restaurant, I found it a bit cramped. The food, however is prepared well and captures all the essence of authentic Thai cuisine. They know how to combine the right amount of spice and zest to bring out the natural flavors of the meat.
Satisfied with food but service was not great.
The food here was amazing!!
terrible service for both dine-in and delivery!!!

I am not sure when/why a lot of reviewers have left a negative comment, but I, along with every single person in my office who's been to this place, love this place, not for its ambiance (its neat, really neat), but for the tasty food they serve!!!!  I (an Indian who loves tongue/throat burning hot/spicy food) am not sure how "authentic"ally Thai the food was, but it was one of the tastiest Thai dishes ("Birds Nest on Fire - Chicken" is the name of the dish) I have ever had. I had specifically requested them to make it as spicy as possible.  Usually most restaurants make spicy, by just adding a lot of red peppers and nothing else!  my 3 other colleagues also loved what they had (i don't remember what they had otherwise I'd have named those dishes too)  A note about the men's restroom: It was very clean, and if I were to enter it blindfolded, I'd think that I am entering a massage room filled with fragrances and scented candles!  A restaurant that has good restrooms, will (most probably) never let you down in terms of food quality and service!  These guys deserve the 5*s!
eggplant dish was excellent.
I was very pleased with the food and takeout service.

This restaurant does not look like much from the street, but the interior is well-decorated.  The service was very good.  The food was up to expectations.  The only negative is that it would be nice to have just one or two familiar foods for kids.  For D.C., the prices were VERY good.  Overall, it was very good.
